HEADWORD: Excogitate
<hw>Ex*cog"i*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Excogitated</conjf> <pr>(#)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos>. <conjf>Excogitating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>excogitatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>excogitare</ets> to excogitate;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>cogitare</ets> to think. See
<er>Cogitate</er>.]</ety> <def>To think out; to find out or discover by
thinking; to devise; to contrive.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Excogitate</xex>
strange arts.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Stirling.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This evidence . . . thus <qex>excogitated</qex> out of the general
